{#-
  Traceability.md.j2 — Bi-directional traceability matrix.

  This template renders [doc/Traceability.md](../Traceability.md) from
  the data exposed by `tools/render_doc.py`:

      project.metadata.{title,version,date,author}
      project.flat_hlrs       — every HLR with section context
      project.flat_llrs       — every LLR with owning function group
      project.flat_tests      — every test sorted by (file, name)
      project.hlrs            — HLRs grouped by section (for §3)
      project.hlr_by_id       — id -> hlr namespace
      project.llr_by_id       — id -> llr namespace
      project.llrs_by_hlr     — hlr_id -> [llr_id, ...]
      project.hlrs_by_sdd     — sdd_ref -> [hlr_id, ...]
      project.tests_by_hlr    — hlr_id -> [test_name, ...]
      project.tests_by_llr    — llr_id -> [test_name, ...]
      project.file_of_test    — test_name -> source file path
      project.sdd_titles      — sdd_ref -> heading title
      project.llrs_no_test    — list of LLR ids unbound to a test
      project.hlrs_no_test    — list of HLR ids unbound to a test
                                (directly or via any of their LLRs)

  Every cross-reference in the matrix is rendered as a clickable
  Markdown link to the artifact's anchor in the upstream document.
-#}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
{%- macro hlr_link(hid) -%}
[`{{ hid }}`](HLRs.md#{{ hid }})
{%- endmacro %}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
{%- macro llr_link(lid) -%}
[`{{ lid }}`](LLRs.md#{{ lid }})
{%- endmacro %}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
{%- macro test_link(tname) -%}
[`{{ tname }}`](STP.md#{{ tname }})
{%- endmacro %}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
{%- macro sdd_link(ref) -%}
{%- set title = project.sdd_titles.get(ref, "") -%}
{%- if title -%}
[§{{ ref }}](SDD.md#{{ (ref + " " + title) | gh_slug }})
{%- else -%}
[§{{ ref }}](SDD.md)
{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro %}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
{%- macro join_hlrs(ids) -%}
{%- if ids -%}
{%- for hid in ids %}{{ hlr_link(hid) }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor -%}
{%- else -%}—{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro %}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
{%- macro join_llrs(ids) -%}
{%- if ids -%}
{%- for lid in ids %}{{ llr_link(lid) }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor -%}
{%- else -%}—{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro %}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
{%- macro join_tests(names) -%}
{%- if names -%}
{%- for tn in names %}{{ test_link(tn) }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor -%}
{%- else -%}**(no test)**{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro %}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
{#- Compute combined test coverage per HLR (direct + via LLRs). -#}
{%- macro tests_for_hlr(hid) -%}
{%- set seen = [] -%}
{%- for tn in project.tests_by_hlr.get(hid, []) -%}
{%- if tn not in seen %}{% set _ = seen.append(tn) %}{% endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- for lid in project.llrs_by_hlr.get(hid, []) -%}
{%- for tn in project.tests_by_llr.get(lid, []) -%}
{%- if tn not in seen %}{% set _ = seen.append(tn) %}{% endif -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{{ join_tests(seen | sort) }}
{%- endmacro %}
{#- ====================================================== -#}
# {{ project.metadata.title }}

**Version:** {{ project.metadata.version }}
**Date:** {{ project.metadata.date }}
**Author(s):** {{ project.metadata.author }}

This document provides the bi-directional traceability between
the four layers of the `{{ project.short_name }}` requirements/design/verification
stack:

1. [Software Design Document](SDD.md) (SDD) — architecture and
   module design.
2. [High-Level Requirements](HLRs.md) (HLR) — externally
   observable behaviour the application must provide.
3. [Low-Level Requirements](LLRs.md) (LLR) — per-function
   behavioural contracts that implement the HLRs.
4. [Software Test Plan](STP.md) and the test artefacts
   under [test/](../test/) — cmocka unit tests and integration
   tests that verify each LLR.

It is generated by `tools/render_doc.py` from the
`<traces>` blocks attached to every HLR, LLR, and test in
[doc/Project.xml](Project.xml). The current snapshot covers
**{{ project.counts.hlrs }} HLRs**, **{{ project.counts.llrs }} LLRs**,
and **{{ project.counts.tests }} tests** across
**{{ project.counts.test_files }} test files**. Every reference
below is a clickable link to the artifact in its source document.

